findings.liver: The liver is diffusely echogenic with a smooth contour. No focal liver mass. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. No ascites.
findings.bile_ducts: No intrahepatic biliary dilation. The common bile duct was not definitely visualized due to a large amount of overlying bowel gas and shadowing from multiple gallbladder stones.
findings.gallbladder: Stones in the distended gallbladder with a thickened and edematous wall, measuring up to 9 mm.
findings.pancreas: Not well visualized, largely obscured by overlying bowel gas.
findings.kidneys: Limited views of the right kidney show no hydronephrosis.
findings.retroperitoneum: Visualized portions of aorta and IVC are within normal limits.
